<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="MainContent" runat="server">
    <h1>Magical Creatures</h1>
    <h3>Treebeard</h3>
    <p>Oldest of the Ents, protector of the forests.
    </p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Treebeard.jpg" style="width: 318px" /></p>
    <h3>Smaug</h3>
    <p>The greatest fire-drake of the Third Age; a powerful, cunning dragon who destroyed Erebor and Dale.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Smaug.jpg" style="width: 343px" /></p>
     <h3>Durin’s Bane</h3>
 <p>The Balrog that dwelt in Moria; a fiery, shadowy demon, one of the corrupted Maia spirits.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Durins%20Bane.jpg" style="width: 319px" /></p>
     <h3>Shelob</h3>
 <p>An enormous ancient spider, last child of Ungoliant, dwelling in the pass of Cirith Ungol.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Shelob.jpg" style="width: 342px; height: 475px" /></p>
     <h3>Gwaihir</h3>
 <p>The Windlord, a great eagle of immense size and intelligence who aids Gandalf.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Gwaihir.jpg" style="width: 476px" /></p>
     <h3>Landroval</h3>
 <p>Brother of Gwaihir, a mighty eagle who helps rescue Frodo and Sam from Mount Doom.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Landroval.jpg" style="width: 445px" /></p>
     <h3>Watcher in the Water</h3>
 <p>A mysterious, tentacled monster guarding the entrance to Moria; origins unknown.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Watcher%20in%20the%20Water.jpg" style="width: 401px" /></p>
     <h3>Ancalagon the Black</h3>
 <p>The greatest dragon ever to live, a massive winged fire-drake destroyed in the First Age.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Ancalagon%20the%20Black.jpg" style="width: 298px" /></p>
     <h3>Glaurung</h3>
 <p>The first of the great dragons, a wingless fire-drake with powerful malice and mind-domination.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Glaurung.jpg" style="width: 330px" /></p>
     <h3>Scatha</h3>
 <p>A long-worm dragon of the Grey Mountains, slain prior to LOTR; his hoard was claimed by the ancestors of the Rohirrim.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<img src="///images/Scatha.jpg" style="width: 279px" /></p>

</asp:Content>
